   <concept id="FAR_7_102" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">7.102</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d401e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d415e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Agencies shall perform acquisition
planning and conduct market research (see <xref href="Part_10.dita#FAR_Part_10"
                        base="i1114815"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  10</xref>) for all acquisitions
in order to promote and provide for—</p>
               <ol id="d401e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d415e19">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Acquisition of commercial products or commercial services, or to the extent that commercial products suitable to meet the agency’s needs are not available, nondevelopmental items, to the maximum extent practicable (<xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3453&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3453</xref>
                           
                         and 41 U.S.C. 3307); and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d415e30">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Full and open competition (see <xref href="Part_6.dita#FAR_Part_6"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>) or, when full and open competition is not required in accordance with <xref href="Part_6.dita#FAR_Part_6"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>, to obtain competition to the maximum extent practicable, with due regard to the nature of the supplies or services to be acquired (<xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3206&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3206(a)(1)</xref>
                           
                         and 41 U.S.C. 3306a)(1)).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d415e47">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Selection
of appropriate contract type in accordance with <xref href="Part_16.dita#FAR_Part_16"
                              base="i1105247"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  16</xref>; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d415e55">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Appropriate
consideration of the use of pre-existing contracts, including interagency
and intra-agency contracts, to fulfill the requirement, before awarding
new contracts. (See <xref href="8.002.dita#FAR_8_002"
                              base="i1118176"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.002</xref> through <xref href="8.004.dita#FAR_8_004"
                              base="i1118226"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.004</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_17.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_17_5"
                              base="i1102787"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  17.5</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d415e69">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> This planning
shall integrate the efforts of all personnel responsible for significant
aspects of the acquisition. The purpose of this planning is to ensure
that the Government meets its needs in the most effective, economical,
and timely manner. Agencies that have a detailed acquisition planning
system in place that generally meets the requirements of <xref href="7.104.dita#FAR_7_104"
                        base="i1118917"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.104</xref> and <xref href="7.105.dita#FAR_7_105"
                        base="i1118935"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.105</xref> need not revise
their system to specifically meet all of these requirements.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
